From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 12:50:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Use a stable DualSense Edge mono endpoint id.

Spider-Man Remastered binds controller effect audio to the Windows MMDevice
identity for the DualSense mono speaker. Standard DualSense already uses a
stable logical endpoint id, so same-model reconnects and DS -> Edge -> DS
switches can route effect audio back to the newly-added Pulse sink.

DualSense Edge speaker sinks can carry raw haptic target metadata, and exposing
them through the standard DualSense logical endpoint id makes Spider-Man crash
while enumerating endpoints. Leaving them on the generated hotplug id is also
wrong, because Edge reconnects appear as a new Windows GUID and the game may
enumerate that endpoint but never activate it after a controller swap.

Give Edge its own model-specific stable endpoint id. This keeps Edge separate
from standard DualSense while preserving a stable app-facing MMDevice identity
across Edge reconnects and DS/DSE model switches. The real Pulse sink is still
used for routing; this only affects the endpoint id exported to mmdevapi.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 17 +++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -1235,10 +1235,18 @@
 {
     /* Edge speaker sinks may also carry raw haptic metadata. They are valid
-     * routing targets, but using the shared mono endpoint id for them makes
-     * Spider-Man Remastered crash while enumerating endpoints at startup. */
+     * routing targets, but using the standard DualSense mono endpoint id for
+     * them makes Spider-Man Remastered crash while enumerating endpoints at
+     * startup. */
     return is_dualsense_speaker_sink(dev) && !dev->raw_haptic_target;
 }
 
+static BOOL is_dualsense_edge_speaker_sink(const PhysDevice *dev)
+{
+    return is_dualsense_speaker_sink(dev) &&
+            (dev->product_id == 0x0df2 ||
+             strstr(dev->pulse_name, "DualSense_Edge_Wireless_Controller"));
+}
+
 static BOOL pulse_name_looks_like_dualsense_speaker_sink(const char *name)
 {
     return name && strstr(name, "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_")
@@ -1286,12 +1294,17 @@
 
 #define DUALSENSE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID \
     "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_Wireless_Controller-00.Default__Speaker__sink"
+#define DUALSENSE_EDGE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID \
+    "alsa_output.usb-Sony_Interactive_Entertainment_DualSense_Edge_Wireless_Controller-00.Default__Speaker__sink"
 
 static BOOL pulse_set_endpoint_id(PhysDevice *dev)
 {
     unsigned int generation;
     size_t len;
 
+    if (is_dualsense_edge_speaker_sink(dev))
+        return !!(dev->endpoint_id = strdup(DUALSENSE_EDGE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID));
+
     if (is_dualsense_endpoint_speaker_sink(dev))
         return !!(dev->endpoint_id = strdup(DUALSENSE_MONO_ENDPOINT_ID));
 
